From: Kamil Bienkiewicz <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 14 May 2026 07:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] dt-bindings: clock: qcom: Add CMN PLL support for IPQ5332 SoC

The CMN PLL block in the IPQ5332 SoC supplies four fixed-rate output
clocks: XO (24 MHz) and sleep (32 kHz) to GCC, and two NSS reference
clocks (200 MHz and 300 MHz) to the NSSCC clock controller that drives
the PPE/EDMA/UNIPHY ethernet stack.

The reference input is the same on-board source the GCC 12gpll block
consumes; for ipq5332-cmn-pll the driver locks the internal VCO and
fans out these four fixed taps.

Signed-off-by: Kamil Bienkiewicz <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
---
 include/dt-bindings/clock/qcom,ipq5332-cmn-pll.h | 19 +++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 19 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 include/dt-bindings/clock/qcom,ipq5332-cmn-pll.h

--- /dev/null
+++ b/include/dt-bindings/clock/qcom,ipq5332-cmn-pll.h
@@ -0,0 +1,19 @@
+/* SPDX-License-Identifier: (GPL-2.0-only OR BSD-2-Clause) */
+/*
+ * Copyright (c) 2026, GL.iNet Flint 3 mainline port.
+ */
+
+#ifndef _DT_BINDINGS_CLK_QCOM_IPQ5332_CMN_PLL_H
+#define _DT_BINDINGS_CLK_QCOM_IPQ5332_CMN_PLL_H
+
+/* CMN PLL core clock. */
+#define IPQ5332_CMN_PLL_CLK			0
+
+/* The fixed-rate output clocks from CMN PLL of IPQ5332. */
+#define IPQ5332_XO_24MHZ_CLK			1
+#define IPQ5332_SLEEP_32KHZ_CLK			2
+#define IPQ5332_NSS_200MHZ_CLK			3
+#define IPQ5332_NSS_300MHZ_CLK			4
+#define IPQ5332_ETH_50MHZ_CLK			5
+
+#endif
